snippet.textDisplay: A lot of maintenance wear parts.  When I get a new car I change all fluid sending samples out, timing belts, serpentine belts, idlers, tensioners, full set of brake pads, brake rotors trying to upgrade the brakes, filters, transmission filter, fuel filters, also brake fluid try to go to dot4 (upgrade).  Then I drive it and my last 3 cars also got springs, shocks, struts,  even inner/outer tie rods, 4 wheel bearings.  Lots of parts but I do them myself.  I makes sure all OBD check engine light are gone then my wife has a good car.  Last one took me about 3 months.  Got it cheap from a bank repo but had to replace a lot on part inside like door panels, front seats, center console but now it is a great car.  Total cost was car $4500, parts at $1600, tags $500 with low mileage the book value is $14,000.  So happy
